# Google Maps SDK keys — Phase 2 (used by the address picker; research R2)
#
# Procurement (manual, one-time, per contributor):
#   1. In the Nafas Google Cloud project, enable:
#        - Maps SDK for iOS
#        - Maps SDK for Android
#      Do NOT enable the Geocoding API — Phase 2 uses
#      `expo-location.reverseGeocodeAsync` instead (research R1).
#   2. Create one API key per platform. Restrict each key:
#        - iOS key:     restrict to the iOS bundle ID
#        - Android key: restrict to the Android package name + debug
#                       and release SHA-1 fingerprints
#   3. Copy this file to `mobile/.env` and paste the keys below.
#      `mobile/.env` is gitignored (.gitignore line 13: `.env*`).
#
# Wiring: `mobile/app.config.ts` reads these via `process.env.*` and
# exposes them under `ios.config.googleMapsApiKey` and
# `android.config.googleMaps.apiKey` for the native Maps SDKs.
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_IOS=""
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_ANDROID=""
